I'm --

262
00:15:24,436 --> 00:15:26,656
Very ashamed of myself...

263
00:15:26,656 --> 00:15:29,809
Once again, I'm sorry...

264
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:34,239
C'mon, now, would you still be cross?

265
00:15:34,239 --> 00:15:38,397
Won't you fix your mood and ask me if I want tea or coffee?

266
00:15:44,190 --> 00:15:46,258
It'd be unfair, Aunt.

267
00:15:46,258 --> 00:15:49,620
Does your heart consent to Reham and Munir's marriage?

268
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:54,720
What does it matter if her heart or mine consents to it?

269
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:57,850
The section of society we belong to

270
00:15:57,850 --> 00:16:01,546
Decides not with their hearts but their minds,

271
00:16:01,546 --> 00:16:05,126
And compromises are valued over happiness.

272
00:16:05,126 --> 00:16:08,847
If her heart's committed the sin of hoping for something,

273
00:16:08,847 --> 00:16:12,967
It'd be better that she atone for it.

274
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:17,624
That <i>is</i> what she'd do.

275
00:16:17,624 --> 00:16:21,606
Bow her head quietly before your honour and your order,

276
00:16:21,606 --> 00:16:23,476
But never be happy.

277
00:16:23,476 --> 00:16:27,726
She'd quietly die from within every single day.

278
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,536
You have to decide, Aunt -

279
00:16:38,536 --> 00:16:42,476
Do you want a life of happiness and satisfaction for Reham,

280
00:16:42,476 --> 00:16:47,620
Or one where she regrets her very existence?

281
00:16:47,620 --> 00:16:50,221
We can't take up arms against the family.

282
00:16:50,221 --> 00:16:51,190
I know.

283
00:16:51,190 --> 00:16:54,941
But Uncle's always done so for the sake of Reham's happiness.

284
00:16:54,941 --> 00:16:57,051
Just talk to him once.

285
00:16:57,051 --> 00:17:01,440
I know he won't be able to refuse after meeting Ashir's family.

286
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:04,267
Besides, he'd invited Ashir himself.

287
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:06,567
Please, Aunt...

288
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,618
Alright.

289
00:17:13,220 --> 00:17:16,971
Ask Ashir to come here with his Mum.

290
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:34,440
Hello?

291
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:38,650
Are you ready to prove your love, Mr Ashir?

292
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,566
What happened?

293
00:17:40,566 --> 00:17:42,081
Nothing <i>yet</i>,

294
00:17:42,081 --> 00:17:45,126
But if you didn't go to Reham's with Aunt,

295
00:17:45,126 --> 00:17:47,760
She'd be married off to her cousin, Munir.

296
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:48,491
W --

297
00:17:48,491 --> 00:17:49,520
W -- What?

298
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,180
Aye.

299
00:17:50,180 --> 00:17:52,181
So you'd better make haste with your proposal

300
00:17:52,181 --> 00:17:53,981
Before he does.

301
00:17:53,981 --> 00:17:55,854
So, hurry up.

302
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:03,280
They asked for time, and you gave them just that, Dad.

303
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:07,880
They'd staved us off on the pretext of her studies before. What is it this time?

304
00:18:08,070 --> 00:18:11,201
It's just a matter of two days; can't you wait?

305
00:18:11,421 --> 00:18:14,340
I don't trust Barkat's intentions.

306
00:18:14,340 --> 00:18:17,490
Don't get too excited. He might even refuse.

307
00:18:17,490 --> 00:18:18,160
Mum --

308
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,426
Please say something good.

309
00:18:19,426 --> 00:18:20,836
Just let him refuse.

310
00:18:20,836 --> 00:18:22,020
Just see what I'll do.

311
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:24,187
He won't refuse.

312
00:18:24,187 --> 00:18:26,627
Do you understand what this refusal means?

313
00:18:26,627 --> 00:18:29,392
He'd have to sever ties with everyone in the family.

314
00:18:29,392 --> 00:18:30,622
Think again, Dad.

315
00:18:30,622 --> 00:18:32,100
Hurry with whatever you're thinking of.

316
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,771
I can't wait much longer.

317
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:40,488
He's out of his mind.

318
00:18:40,488 --> 00:18:42,256
Talk to Barkat quickly.

319
00:18:42,256 --> 00:18:45,206
I'm afraid he may do something.

320
00:18:48,350 --> 00:18:49,607
Oh?

321
00:18:49,607 --> 00:18:51,508
That's splendid.

322
00:18:51,508 --> 00:18:53,507
Quickly now, talk to Sofia.

323
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:56,008
How can I talk to Mum, Appa Bi?

324
00:18:56,008 --> 00:19:01,790
She'd strongly emphasised that I focus only on the business, and that was my intention, too.

325
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:03,706
I didn't know such a situation would come up.

326
00:19:03,706 --> 00:19:06,557
You know fully well how much she loves you,

327
00:19:06,557 --> 00:19:08,250
How she dotes on you.

328
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,017
She'd be delighted and not angry.

329
00:19:10,017 --> 00:19:12,118
Just talk to her for once.

330
00:19:12,287 --> 00:19:14,918
What if she got angry?

331
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:18,167
Leave it to me.

332
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:20,216
Besides, even if she got angry with you,

333
00:19:20,216 --> 00:19:21,550
It'd only be for a moment.

334
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:24,237
But if your love got angry with you,

335
00:19:24,237 --> 00:19:28,007
What would you do about your own heartache?

336
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:34,696
For the first time in my life, I've apologised to someone on your insistence.

337
00:19:34,696 --> 00:19:37,356
If this didn't bear fruit...

338
00:19:37,356 --> 00:19:39,667
What are you talking about!

339
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:42,306
Why wouldn't it bear fruit?

340
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:44,550
Love is a powerful force.

341
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,127
And wily love

342
00:19:46,127 --> 00:19:47,872
And wily love is exceptionally powerful.

343
00:19:47,872 --> 00:19:50,093
Good Lord...!

344
00:19:51,562 --> 00:19:55,502
Got to admit, you've done a rather exceptional duty as a wife!

345
00:19:56,053 --> 00:20:01,490
Not once did it occur to me

346
00:20:01,490 --> 00:20:05,110
That there could be no better suitor for our Farah than Ashir.

347
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,616
Just wait and watch.

348
00:20:06,616 --> 00:20:09,401
Our Farah would rule over there.

349
00:20:09,401 --> 00:20:11,606
And do you know the best part?

350
00:20:11,606 --> 00:20:14,536
Sofia thought the same way, too.

351
00:20:14,536 --> 00:20:16,480
She said to me immediately,

352
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,236
'Don't worry about Farah'.

353
00:20:18,236 --> 00:20:20,977
'Farah's <i>my</i> daughter'.

