366
00:20:45,472 --> 00:20:46,741
<i>Come here</i>

367
00:20:46,741 --> 00:20:49,393
<i>Don't keep me waiting...</i>

368
00:20:49,393 --> 00:20:53,165
<i>This ambience is blossoming once again,</i>

369
00:20:53,165 --> 00:20:56,225
<i>The ambience of this redolent world</i>

370
00:20:56,225 --> 00:20:59,616
<i>And the Heavens are humming a melody once again</i>

371
00:20:59,616 --> 00:21:03,917
<i>Come here already, my beloved...</i>

372
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,276
Come in.

373
00:21:27,276 --> 00:21:27,916
Hey!

374
00:21:27,916 --> 00:21:30,566
You haven't gone to bed yet, Ashir!

375
00:21:30,566 --> 00:21:33,016
Mum -- I --

376
00:21:33,016 --> 00:21:35,450
I wanted to talk to you about something.

377
00:21:35,450 --> 00:21:37,726
Come and sit.

378
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:51,480
What is it? Why are you thinking so much?

379
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:57,360
I'm not sure how I should ask you...

380
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:59,540
It's --

381
00:21:59,540 --> 00:22:03,401
Just that you've given me everything in life without my having to ask for it.

382
00:22:03,401 --> 00:22:08,770
You've fulfilled every wish and given me every happiness before I could say a word.

383
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:10,050
Now --

384
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:13,180
Now when I'm asking for something for the first time, I don't know --

385
00:22:13,180 --> 00:22:14,686
How to ask for it.

386
00:22:14,686 --> 00:22:18,256
In that case, I should be the one who's worried.

387
00:22:18,256 --> 00:22:22,940
What is it that gives my son happiness that I've got no idea about?

388
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:26,980
No -- Mum -- It's not like that --

389
00:22:26,980 --> 00:22:28,537
The thing is --

390
00:22:28,537 --> 00:22:30,937
It wasn't planned at all --

391
00:22:30,937 --> 00:22:33,880
I wanted to focus completely on the business --

392
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:36,550
Bu -- Now -- Th --

393
00:22:36,991 --> 00:22:40,201
You like her very much, don't you?

394
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:41,916
Mum?

395
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:44,450
How --

396
00:22:44,450 --> 00:22:46,251
Appa Bi?

397
00:22:46,251 --> 00:22:49,632
It's etched on your face.

398
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:51,702
And once again,

399
00:22:51,702 --> 00:22:55,292
You didn't have to ask for it.

400
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:01,896
You'll have no complaints from me, Mum.

401
00:23:01,896 --> 00:23:04,256
I'd focus all my attention on the business.

402
00:23:04,256 --> 00:23:05,776
Please, just for once,

403
00:23:05,776 --> 00:23:08,517
Come with me...
-When are we going?

404
00:23:08,972 --> 00:23:10,186
Tomorrow evening.

405
00:23:10,186 --> 00:23:11,357
Done.

406
00:23:11,357 --> 00:23:12,737
Thank you, Mum!

407
00:23:12,737 --> 00:23:14,127
I love you so much!

408
00:23:14,127 --> 00:23:15,897
Thank you!

409
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:26,990
<i>O Lord! You know my predicament</i>

410
00:23:26,990 --> 00:23:33,000
<i>My life has become an affliction</i>

411
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:39,969
<i>Every gasp weighs at me</i>

412
00:23:39,969 --> 00:23:45,582
<i>Why don't these doleful nights come to pass?</i>

413
00:23:45,582 --> 00:23:52,390
<i>How do I recount what has befallen me</i>

414
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:54,937
Ashir here.
<i>Why is every last vestige of love immured?</i>

415
00:23:54,937 --> 00:23:59,226
<i>Why is every last vestige of love immured?</i>

416
00:23:59,226 --> 00:24:06,066
<i>How do I recount what has befallen me</i>

417
00:24:06,066 --> 00:24:13,227
<i>Why is every last vestige of love immured?</i>

418
00:24:14,726 --> 00:24:16,210
Hello?

419
00:24:17,977 --> 00:24:23,087
I didn't know you were more eager to become mine than I was to make you mine!

420
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:26,870
Anyway, don't worry.

421
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:29,070
Let me tell you your wait's over.

422
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:31,838
Mum and I will be there tomorrow.

423
00:24:34,990 --> 00:24:38,440
Tell Uncle that I'll not be coming just for tea.

424
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:42,124
I'd be coming to take his most precious treasure.

425
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,640
<i>Come here, my beloved</i>

426
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:38,300
<i>Come here</i>

427
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:40,061
<i>Come here, my beloved</i>

428
00:25:40,061 --> 00:25:41,822
<i>Come here</i>

429
00:25:41,822 --> 00:25:43,491
<i>Come here, my beloved</i>

430
00:25:43,491 --> 00:25:44,771
<i>Come here</i>

431
00:25:44,771 --> 00:25:48,951
<i>Don't keep me waiting...</i>

432
00:25:50,801 --> 00:25:51,603
Splendid.

433
00:25:51,603 --> 00:25:53,354
You'd invited him yourself,

434
00:25:53,354 --> 00:25:54,903
And now you're asking, 'Who is it'?

435
00:25:54,903 --> 00:25:58,093
Who are you talking about?

436
00:25:58,093 --> 00:26:00,160
Oh --

437
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:04,500
The lad who'd come to drop Reham the other day? He had such a nice name... Whatzit...
-Ashir.

438
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:07,346
Ah, right, Ashir. I'd forgotten.

439
00:26:07,346 --> 00:26:10,650
Yes... I'd invited himself myself.

440
00:26:10,650 --> 00:26:12,056
He'd called, too.

441
00:26:12,056 --> 00:26:14,020
Reham had turned him down,

442
00:26:14,020 --> 00:26:16,806
I told her to ask Dad first.

443
00:26:16,806 --> 00:26:19,970
No, turning him down would be improper.

444
00:26:19,970 --> 00:26:25,290
Besides, a guest is a blessing from the Lord. And anyhow, I'd invited him myself.

445
00:26:25,290 --> 00:26:26,778
When's he coming?

446
00:26:26,778 --> 00:26:27,907
6 o'clock.

447
00:26:27,907 --> 00:26:29,690
6 o'clock...

448
00:26:29,690 --> 00:26:30,719
Alright.

449
00:26:30,719 --> 00:26:33,249
Regale them when they're here.

450
00:26:33,249 --> 00:26:35,886
Let me know if I have to get anything to eat.

451
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:37,888
No, we have everything at home.

452
00:26:37,888 --> 00:26:39,076
Alright, then.

453
00:26:39,076 --> 00:26:40,920
I'll get going.

454
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:43,076
Bye.

455
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:50,841
Thank you, Mum.

456
00:26:50,841 --> 00:26:52,390
May you live long, my dear.

457
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:55,040
You're happy now, aren't you?

458
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:20,606
You've acted like an outsider, now, haven't you?

459
00:27:20,606 --> 00:27:22,866
How many times had I asked you to tell you, but no...

460
00:27:22,866 --> 00:27:24,217
You ignored it.

461
00:27:24,217 --> 00:27:26,128
Alright, fair enough...

462
00:27:26,517 --> 00:27:29,150
Everything happened so suddenly, mate... I couldn't tell anything.

463
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,959
Everything happened so suddenly, mate... I couldn't tell anything.
-I'm not a kid who'd be satisfied to hear this.

464
00:27:31,959 --> 00:27:34,670
What I'd been suspecting for long has happened at last.

465
00:27:34,670 --> 00:27:36,566
Alright, you know now, don't you?

466
00:27:36,566 --> 00:27:37,670
Are you happy now?

467
00:27:37,670 --> 00:27:39,316
You didn't even tell me now.

468
00:27:39,316 --> 00:27:43,986
Appa Bi broke the news that we're going to meet my sister-in-law in the evening.

469
00:27:46,286 --> 00:27:47,957
Sorry...

470
00:27:48,457 --> 00:27:50,688
Just a sorry won't do.

471
00:27:50,688 --> 00:27:54,908
How can you select my sister-in-law without my approval?

472
00:27:55,628 --> 00:27:57,078
She's so good

473
00:27:57,078 --> 00:27:59,869
That you'd approve of her the moment you see her.

474
00:27:59,869 --> 00:28:01,819
You have no idea

475
00:28:01,819 --> 00:28:04,250
How tough my selection criteria are.

476
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:06,331
Ask her to brace herself.

477
00:28:06,331 --> 00:28:09,521
You should brace yourself too. There's a surprise coming your way.

478
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:11,401
So confident!

479
00:28:11,401 --> 00:28:12,921
Yes.

480
00:28:13,122 --> 00:28:15,011
Are you happy?

481
00:28:16,874 --> 00:28:18,104
Very.

482
00:28:18,104 --> 00:28:20,975
That meets my selection criteria.

483
00:28:21,810 --> 00:28:24,020
Thanks for understanding, man!

484
00:28:24,510 --> 00:28:26,326
Alright, tell me, what should I wear?

485
00:28:26,326 --> 00:28:28,297
I'm so confused...

486
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:33,720
I think this one will work.

487
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:34,750
This one?

488
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:36,731
Yeah.

489
00:28:37,630 --> 00:28:44,496
<i>Tear me to shreds</i>

490
00:28:44,496 --> 00:28:51,426
<i>Like a modiste tears rags</i>

491
00:28:51,426 --> 00:28:58,190
<i>No one has ever been able to tame the mind</i>

492
00:28:58,190 --> 00:29:03,579
<i>No one has been able to chain it</i>

493
00:29:03,579 --> 00:29:07,306
<i>He who understood the 'a' of amour</i>

494
00:29:07,306 --> 00:29:10,379
<i>Dares not take up arms against fate</i>

495
00:29:10,379 --> 00:29:13,886
<i>He who understood the 'm,' 'o,' 'u,' and 'r', O Bulleya,</i>

496
00:29:13,886 --> 00:29:19,516
<i>Found himself reduced to a fakir.</i>

497
00:29:29,500 --> 00:29:31,126
Right...

498
00:29:35,020 --> 00:29:36,130
Wait.

499
00:29:36,130 --> 00:29:37,496
I'll see.

500
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:41,586
Yes, I'm coming.

501
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:51,800
Hello.
-Hello.

502
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:53,966
How are you?
-By the Lord's grace, I'm fine.

503
00:29:53,966 --> 00:29:57,546
Hello. Please, come inside.
-Hello.

504
00:29:57,736 --> 00:29:59,997
How are you, Shakira?

505
00:30:00,186 --> 00:30:01,636
I'm fine.

506
00:30:01,636 --> 00:30:02,457
Hello.

507
00:30:02,457 --> 00:30:04,532
Hello.
-Hello.

508
00:30:04,718 --> 00:30:05,668
Please,

509
00:30:05,668 --> 00:30:07,878
Come and sit inside.

510
00:30:07,878 --> 00:30:09,478
Here.

511
00:30:10,820 --> 00:30:12,236
Come.

512
00:30:13,076 --> 00:30:14,757
After you.

513
00:30:36,390 --> 00:30:37,420
Mum...

514
00:30:37,420 --> 00:30:40,500
What if Ashir and his family showed up before <i>them</i>?

515
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:42,900
God forbid that anything like that happen!

516
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:45,280
I'll serve them some tea

517
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:47,345
And get them going real quick.

518
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:48,310
Now,

519
00:30:48,310 --> 00:30:50,590
May the Lord be so kind...

520
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:04,270
Ashir, Adan, quickly, now, we'll be late.

521
00:31:05,270 --> 00:31:06,790
I'm already ready, Mum.

522
00:31:06,790 --> 00:31:08,973
It's Ashir who's taking so long...

523
00:31:08,973 --> 00:31:11,941
He's going to meet his bride. He, of all the people, would get ready proper.

524
00:31:11,941 --> 00:31:13,962
In hindsight, it's good that my trip got cancelled.

525
00:31:13,962 --> 00:31:15,716
I'd have missed all of this.

526
00:31:15,716 --> 00:31:16,687
Right...

527
00:31:16,687 --> 00:31:17,766
The trip

528
00:31:17,766 --> 00:31:20,538
The trip you were going on on Ashir's recommendation.

529
00:31:20,538 --> 00:31:22,738
You never turn him down.

530
00:31:22,738 --> 00:31:25,650
For instance, this, right now. Here he said it, and there you agreed.

531
00:31:25,650 --> 00:31:28,176
Because he always obeys me.

532
00:31:28,176 --> 00:31:31,399
I'm a bit impish, innit, Mum?

533
00:31:31,637 --> 00:31:32,936
<i>Just</i> a bit?

534
00:31:32,936 --> 00:31:34,570
Get going already.

535
00:31:34,570 --> 00:31:37,646
We'd get going once he's here.

536
00:31:37,890 --> 00:31:39,040
R --

537
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:41,336
R -- Rehmat...

538
00:31:41,336 --> 00:31:42,526
One can't decide

539
00:31:42,526 --> 00:31:45,256
So quickly...

540
00:31:45,256 --> 00:31:47,176
Just let me

541
00:31:47,176 --> 00:31:51,066
Ask Reham what she thinks...

542
00:31:54,100 --> 00:31:56,526
What <i>Reham</i> thinks?

543
00:31:56,827 --> 00:32:00,867
Barkat, the elders have always taken decisions

544
00:32:00,867 --> 00:32:02,917
For the daughters.

545
00:32:02,917 --> 00:32:05,648
That's fine,

546
00:32:05,648 --> 00:32:10,870
But my Reham is different from the other daughters of the family.

547
00:32:10,870 --> 00:32:15,651
She's educated, so what she thinks --
-Oh?

548
00:32:15,651 --> 00:32:17,801
What do you want to say, Barkat?

549
00:32:17,801 --> 00:32:20,082
Are our daughters unlettered?

550
00:32:20,082 --> 00:32:23,725
No -- Surely, he didn't mean that -- you --

551
00:32:23,725 --> 00:32:26,610
I can understand what you mean very well.

552
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:29,760
Reham's taken a liking to someone from her University.

553
00:32:29,760 --> 00:32:31,866
This is why you're saying all of this.

554
00:32:31,866 --> 00:32:33,806
Rehmat...

555
00:32:33,806 --> 00:32:36,457
My Reham is not like that.

556
00:32:36,457 --> 00:32:39,117
She'd gone to the University to study!

557
00:32:39,117 --> 00:32:42,487
Girls don't <i>just</i> study,

558
00:32:42,487 --> 00:32:45,750
They also find high-born suitors in the name of love.

559
00:32:45,750 --> 00:32:47,086
They also find high-born suitors in the name of love.
-Enough!

560
00:32:47,086 --> 00:32:48,667
My Reham is not like that.

561
00:32:48,667 --> 00:32:49,438
Oh?

562
00:32:49,438 --> 00:32:51,270
But why are you so angry, then?

563
00:32:51,270 --> 00:32:53,480
I didn't even mention Reham.

564
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,950
It must be your conscience speaking out...

565
00:32:55,950 --> 00:32:57,326
If that's not the case,

566
00:32:57,326 --> 00:33:00,637
Just get Reham and Munir married.

567
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:05,129
But remember this, Barkat,

568
00:33:05,129 --> 00:33:06,870
If Reham

569
00:33:06,870 --> 00:33:10,410
Married someone she likes,

570
00:33:10,410 --> 00:33:14,966
I'll make sure you're banished from the kin.

571
00:33:16,670 --> 00:33:20,246
You'll be utterly disgraced.

572
00:33:22,850 --> 00:33:26,456
I'm a man of great dignity.

573
00:33:26,846 --> 00:33:30,026
I trust my daughter completely.

574
00:33:30,026 --> 00:33:32,380
The day this trust breaks, I promise you,

575
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:35,710
You won't have to do a thing.

576
00:33:35,710 --> 00:33:41,086
I swear by the Lord, I'd slit my own throat.

577
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:59,496
Remember this vow, Barkat,

578
00:33:59,496 --> 00:34:01,550
And, when it's time, honour it.

579
00:34:01,550 --> 00:34:03,230
Come, Parveen.

580
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:23,279
Everything's gone to waste.

581
00:34:23,279 --> 00:34:26,849
I was out of my mind to fall for everything you and Suboor had said.

582
00:34:26,849 --> 00:34:28,220
Call him

583
00:34:28,220 --> 00:34:29,337
And tell him

584
00:34:29,337 --> 00:34:31,303
Not to come.

585
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:37,626
Haven't you heard

586
00:34:37,626 --> 00:34:40,317
What your Dad has sworn to do?

587
00:34:40,317 --> 00:34:41,438
It'd be the end of the world

588
00:34:41,438 --> 00:34:43,010
If they showed up.

589
00:34:43,010 --> 00:34:44,026
Call them quickly.

590
00:34:44,026 --> 00:34:46,248
They'd better not come.

591
00:35:22,710 --> 00:35:25,690
It seems you're growing restless by the moment!

592
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:28,891
Please don't come here...

593
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:31,206
What happened, Reham?

594
00:35:31,206 --> 00:35:33,299
Is everything alright? Why are you crying?

595
00:35:33,299 --> 00:35:34,249
Ashir --

596
00:35:34,249 --> 00:35:36,680
I don't have the answer to your questions --

597
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:38,131
Just -- You're not coming here.

598
00:35:38,131 --> 00:35:38,693
B --

599
00:35:38,693 --> 00:35:40,604
B -- But you'd said --

600
00:35:40,604 --> 00:35:41,795
B -- But you'd said --
-Forget it!

601
00:35:41,795 --> 00:35:45,237
Just forget anything I'd ever said!

602
00:35:46,246 --> 00:35:49,459
If you have an ounce of love for me in your heart,

603
00:35:49,459 --> 00:35:52,067
Just an ounce,

604
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:54,848
For the sake of that love,

605
00:35:54,848 --> 00:35:57,558
Forget everything.

606
00:35:59,540 --> 00:36:03,936
I can't pay the price of your love.

607
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:06,900
Hello --?

